ast.name: RPN Calculator
ast.comment: A HP-like pocket calculator with a four-level stack and reverse polish notation (see http://www.hpmuseum.org/rpn.htm). Online help: Press g, ? to read the manual! This is all integrated. Web access is only needed to open the above http link directly from the help pages, not to read the manual. 2012-10-14: Display formats with 0 digit do not append decimal symbol any more. Better contrast when run in light color theme. Fixed a typo in help screen. Slightly refined key label positions.

body.text: Visual feedback for the pressed key:
1: transform (x,y) to (x',y') after entering a point
2: transform (a',b') to (a,b) after calculating the linear regression

thenBody.text: linear form is: ln y = ln a + bx
linear form is: ln y = ln a + b ln x
plot spikes to the original data points
